Package org.jreliability.function

Interface ReliabilityFunction

All Superinterfaces:
Function
All Known Implementing Classes:
BarlowProschan.BarlowProschanFunction, BDDReliabilityFunction, ConstantFailureFunction, ConstantReliabilityFunction, ExponentialFailureFunction, ExponentialReliabilityFunction, HjorthReliabilityFunction, LognormalReliabilityFunction, NMWDReliabilityFunction, NormalReliabilityFunction, ParallelReliabilityFunction, ReliabilityFunctionSet, SampledReliabilityFunction, SerialReliabilityFunction, SLReliabilityFunction, SumReliabilityFunction, WeibullReliabilityFunction
public interface ReliabilityFunction extends Function
The ReliabilityFunction represents a reliability or survival function R(x) that is commonly defined as
R(x) = 1 - F(x),
with F(x) being a UnreliabilityFunction F(x).

The reliability function gives at time x the probability that the object of interest survives beyond x.
